servings: 2
---

250 g Ground Pork
113 g Spring Mix
113 g Baby Tomatoes
3 tbsp Guacamole
2 tbsp Ranch Dressing
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
28 g Croutons
3 unit(s) Radish
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
0.06 tsp Pepper*
0.06 tsp Salt*
1 tbsp Oil*

Slice radish into 1/4-inch rounds.
Add guacamole and ranch to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk together.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then pork. Cook, breaking up pork into large pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Add Zesty Garlic Spice Blend and cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1 min. Season with salt and pepper.

Add spring mix, croutons, radishes and tomatoes to the large bowl with dressing. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine.

Divide salad between bowls.
Top with pork and cheese.

If you've opted to get pork, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the turkey.